# Commits

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

```
type(scope): imperative subject

Optional body explaining why, not what.
```

## Types

| Type | When |
|------|------|
| `feat` | New feature or story implementation |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `test` | Adding or updating tests only |
| `docs` | Documentation or tracker-only updates |
| `chore` | Tooling, deps, config |
| `refactor` | Code change without behavior change |

## Scope

Optional area: `tracker`, `auth`, `ui`, `docs`, `ci`, story ID (`story-2.1`)

## Subject

- Imperative mood ("add", not "added")
- Lowercase, no trailing period
- Max ~72 characters
- Reference story ID when the change implements a tracker ticket

## Examples

```
feat(story-2.1): add login flow with JWT validation
test(story-2.1): add AC1 and AC2 acceptance tests
docs(tracker): mark STORY-2.1 DONE after audit
chore: add husky pre-commit hook
```

## Rules

- Never commit unless explicitly asked.
- Never skip hooks (`--no-verify`) unless explicitly requested.
- Never commit secrets (`.env`, credentials).
